I'm in a similar situation. I need to set up a new website, currently sorting out my requirements in terms of accessibility and privacy (so no tools like Google Analytics), and researching how to do video calls via Signal; it requires a lot of client education, but I think it's worth it.
I'm happy to share my experience with you both, and I'm confident you'll be able to do it!
Website: you can take a look at @user5. It seems easy to use, has a nice interface, and is open-source. I plan to migrate one of my websites to it before my next renewal.
Signal: take a look at cal.com. It's an open-source calendar service that integrates scheduling for video calls with Element, Jitsi, and it also supports Signal, but I haven't tested whether it's just for messaging or for video calls as well.
I can recommend @user6. It's end-to-end encrypted, decentralized, and open-source.
